The paper deals with automatic thumbnail generation using deep neural networks, which is a computer vision task and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep neural networks also suggests that it could belong to machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves data collection and training of the model, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of neural networks for image processing and generation suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as well.
